<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-31T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="1087" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1087">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.01/5–2945: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister to Syria and Lebanon</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-31T19:00:00-04:00">May 31,
                                    1945—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>162. Reurtel 161, May 29. Dept feels that it is for the Lebanese Govt
                            alone to determine countries to which it may make treaty proposals and
                            that the matter is not one in which this Govt could give advice with
                            propriety.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>